-- Exxon CEO sees U.S. difficulty competing for LNG
-- 
-- Wed Mar 5, 2008 1:52pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/05/us-exxon-lng-idUSN0561948920080305

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Exxon Mobil Corp ( XOM.N ) Chief Executive Rex Tillerson said the United States will have trouble competing with Asia and Europe for liquefied natural gas in coming years. 

 "In the near term, that's going to be the situation. The U.S., from a pricing standpoint will have difficulty competing for LNG," he said, speaking to analysts in New York. (Reporting by  Michael Erman ; Editing by  Derek Caney )